00:45:39,650 --> 00:45:41,569
 They can become
 proficient readers

970
00:45:41,570 --> 00:45:43,869
 and they can get their
 self-esteem back.

971
00:45:43,870 --> 00:45:45,949
 It's not a hopeless situation.

972
00:45:45,950 --> 00:45:48,309
 But it does require
 work on your part.

973
00:45:48,310 --> 00:45:50,249
 You will have to do research.

974
00:45:50,250 --> 00:45:52,779
 You will have to educate
 yourself so that you can learn

975
00:45:52,780 --> 00:45:55,209
 how best to support
 your child at home

976
00:45:55,210 --> 00:45:57,869
 and advocate for him in school.

977
00:45:57,870 --> 00:46:01,169
 Teachers-- how many of you
 have students in your classroom

978
00:46:01,170 --> 00:46:05,449
who seem so smart but yet
 they struggle so much?

979
00:46:05,450 --> 00:46:08,319
 How often have you been banging
 your head against the wall,

980
00:46:08,320 --> 00:46:11,259
 trying to figure out what you
 can do to help this child,

981
00:46:11,260 --> 00:46:13,369
 believing there is
 an answer but not

982
00:46:13,370 --> 00:46:15,769
knowing where to
 find that answer?

983
00:46:15,770 --> 00:46:19,129
 Take it upon yourself to
 learn more about dyslexia.

984
00:46:19,130 --> 00:46:21,059
 You can help give
 parents an answer

985
00:46:21,060 --> 00:46:24,069
 and you can be the reason
 a child with dyslexia

986
00:46:24,070 --> 00:46:26,549
 will find the road
 to success, instead

987
00:46:26,550 --> 00:46:29,159
 of the road of
 constant struggle.

988
00:46:29,160 --> 00:46:32,899
 Schools-- if your primary
 function is to educate all

989
00:46:32,900 --> 00:46:35,649
 children, then you cannot
 keep turning a blind eye

990
00:46:35,650 --> 00:46:37,519
 to something that
 affects one out

991
00:46:37,520 --> 00:46:40,009
 of five of your
 student population.

992
00:46:40,010 --> 00:46:42,519
 Dyslexia is real.

993
00:46:42,520 --> 00:46:45,139
 And please understand
 that early dyslexia

994
00:46:45,140 --> 00:46:47,799
 screening and
 intervention is smart.

995
00:46:47,800 --> 00:46:49,219
 It makes sense.

996
00:46:49,220 --> 00:46:52,459
 It saves time and money
 and most importantly, it

997
00:46:52,460 --> 00:46:55,829
 removes roadblocks that can
 keep our children with dyslexia

998
00:46:55,830 --> 00:46:58,169
 from reaching their
 full potential.

999
00:46:58,170 --> 00:47:01,789
 And finally, policymakers--
 you have the ability

1000
00:47:01,790 --> 00:47:04,979
 to pass laws that make it
 mandatory for all schools

1001
00:47:04,980 --> 00:47:08,059
 to screen every single
 student for dyslexia.

1002
00:47:08,060 --> 00:47:10,209
 And to also provide
 children with dyslexia

1003
00:47:10,210 --> 00:47:12,589
 was scientifically
 proven instruction.

1004
00:47:12,590 --> 00:47:15,539
 You also have the ability
 to pass laws that require

1005
00:47:15,540 --> 00:47:18,889
 every teacher training college
